info.name: 10. Use Case - Skrining Hipotiroid Kongenital (SHK)
info.description:
For **complete repository for all SATUSEHAT use-cases** please access our public workspaces : [Postman Workspaces](https://s.id/PostmanSATUSEHAT)

For **detailed SATUSEHAT use-cases import link** please see : [Postman Public Kemkes Link](https://link.kemkes.go.id/PostmanSATUSEHAT)

Any information about SATUSEHAT FHIR Profile could be accessed through [Simplifier FHIR Profile](https://simplifier.net/guide/SATUSEHAT-FHIR-R4-Implementation-Guide/Home/FHIRProfiles?version=current)

> This use case folder is heavily parameterized to help with onboarding on SHK module. Please kindly check each tests tab that exists (have green button on tests). 
  
> Interoperability Engineering team in DTO have provided assistance to GET several observations, procedures, medicationStatement, and Condition as per mandatory for referral procedure of SHK referral from first line clinics to hospitals/laboratories. 
  
> Test cases highlighting the parameterization can be seen in GET ServiceRequest by National Referral Number, and also in all GET - ALL requests, which filters the mandatory observations, etc. as per 27 Jan 2024 and helps to save the uuid the GET with the next requests. 
  
> Encounters, serviceRequests etc has also been parameterized for the example resources for referred lab to use. 
  

| **Folder History** | **Editor** | **Date** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| First Upload | [jaisyullah.islam@dto.kemkes.go.id](https://mailto:jaisyullah.islam@dto.kemkes.go.id) | 12-06-2023 |
| Update according to latest Playbook, heavy parameterization used (please see tests in each payload) | [thomas.chaidir@dto.kemkes.go.id](https://mailto:thomas.chaidir@dto.kemkes.go.id) | 28-01-2024 |
